<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="7" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/10934a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-28T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 28,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>62. If you can informally arrange to be given copies of minutes of
                            meetings of Conference of Ambassadors it would be of great value to the
                            Department to continue to receive them. Telegraphic summaries are
                            unnecessary except of discussions important to the United States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>